  "prompt": "What test cases management tool do you recommend to integrate with Github or Zenhub?",
  "response": "There are several test case management tools that integrate well with GitHub or Zephyr. Here are some recommended options:\n\n1. TestRail\n- Robust integration with GitHub\n- Comprehensive test management features\n- Detailed reporting and tracking\n- Supports manual and automated testing\n- Pricing varies based on team size\n\n2. Zephyr Scale (formerly Test Management for Jira)\n- Native Jira integration\n- GitHub integration via webhooks\n- Good for Agile teams\n- Supports test planning and execution\n- Reasonable pricing\n\n3. qTest\n- Strong GitHub integration\n- Supports Agile and DevOps workflows\n- Advanced reporting\n- Real-time synchronization\n- Enterprise-level features\n\n4. PractiTest\n- GitHub integration\n- Flexible test management\n- Multiple view options\n- Good for small to medium teams\n- Competitive pricing\n\n5. Azure Test Plans\n- Microsoft ecosystem integration\n- Direct GitHub connection\n- Part of Azure DevOps\n- Good for teams using Microsoft tools\n\nRecommendation depends on:\n- Team size\n- Budget\n- Specific integration requirements\n- Existing toolchain\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these options?",
